-- Polyus Gold, Norilsk Nickel, Gazprom May Move Today: Russian Stock Preview
-- Maria Kolesnikova
-- 2010-06-18T05:18:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/polyus-gold-norilsk-nickel-gazprom-may-move-today-russian-stock-preview.html

          
          
             The following shares may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the previous close unless
otherwise noted.  
 The 30-stock  Micex Index  retreated 1 percent to 1,356.18 in
Moscow. The dollar-denominated  RTS Index  fell 0.1 percent to
1,400.66.  
 OAO Polyus Gold  (PLZL RX): Gold traded near a record high
as the dollar weakened on signs the U.S. recovery may slow and
on concern the European sovereign-debt crisis will persist.
Russia’s largest gold producer rose 1.2 percent to 1,509.99
rubles.  
 OAO Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper fell the most in
almost two weeks in London and New York after reports signaled
an uneven economic rebound in the U.S., the world’s second-
biggest consumer of the metal. Nickel also fell. Russia’s
largest mining company retreated 2.9 percent to 4,945.86 rubles.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): Russia’s gas export monopoly said it
may cut 85 percent of its supplies to Belarus if the country
fails to pay its debt for gas delivered this year. Gazprom slid
1.2 percent to 156.65 rubles.  
